cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with image segmentation using deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and dynamic programming (DP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses end-to-end learning and optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of synthetic gradients (SG) is a novel technique that involves training neural networks, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the universal function approximation property of neural networks, which is a topic in neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
